📄 Project Report (100–150 Words)

While researching online safety and cybercrime, I was surprised to learn that many cyber fraud cases occur because of simple human mistakes rather than advanced hacking. Most attackers rely on social engineering, creating urgency or fear to trick people into sharing OTPs or approving payments. I was especially surprised that entering a UPI PIN always authorizes a payment, yet many students misunderstand this.

As a result of this research, I will personally adopt the habit of carefully checking every payment request before approving it and verifying suspicious messages before clicking on any links. I will also ensure that two-factor authentication is enabled on all important accounts. This task helped me understand that awareness and cautious online behavior are the most effective ways to prevent cybercrime.
